.TH "pdc_instr" 9 "pdc_instr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pdc_instr \- Get instruction that invokes PDCE_CHECK in HPMC handler.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pdc_instr
.BI "(unsigned int *instr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "instr" 12
Pointer to variable which will get instruction opcode.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The return value is PDC_OK (0) in case call succeeded.
